<h2>Overview</h2><p>Installing a Rotopax fuel can onto your Poison Spyder body mount tire carrier can significantly enhance your Jeep's off-road capabilities. This tutorial will walk you through the process and provide insights into the best practices for a secure and practical installation.</p><h2>What This Covers</h2><p>In this article, we will cover the step-by-step process of installing a Rotopax using the deluxe mount on a 2015 Jeep Wrangler JK. We’ll discuss tools required, installation tips, and practical considerations to ensure that your fuel can is mounted securely and effectively.</p><h2>Step-by-Step Breakdown</h2><ol><li><strong>Gather Your Supplies:</strong> Before getting started, ensure you have all the tools and materials needed. This includes the Rotopax RX-DLX-PM Deluxe Pack Mount, a rotary tool for drilling (if necessary), threadlock, 1/4 by 20 bolts (length based on your setup), nylock nuts, and washers.</li><li><strong>Attach the Bracket to the Mount:</strong> Begin by attaching the mounting bracket to the Rotopax mount itself. Use threadlock on the bolts for added security to prevent them from loosening over time.</li><li><strong>Prepare the Tire Carrier:</strong> Identify the pre-drilled holes on your Poison Spyder tire carrier that are designated for Rotopax mounts. If the holes are slightly undersized, use a drill to widen them for the bolts to fit.</li><li><strong>Securely Install the Assembly:</strong> Mount the combined assembly to your tire carrier, ensuring that the angle of the Rotopax is horizontal to the ground. This is crucial for functionality and stability, as it prevents potential spillage during off-road excursions.</li><li><strong>Final Adjustments:</strong> Once mounted, check the alignment and ensure it clears when the tire carrier is opened. Adjust as needed, and consider your future needs—like adding another Rotopax fuel can!</li></ol><h2>Helpful Tips</h2><p>Here are some tips to keep in mind during this installation:</p><ul><li><strong>Use High-Quality Fasteners:</strong> Investing in durable bolts and nuts is essential for heavy-duty applications like fuel storage.</li><li><strong>Plan for Venting:</strong> Remember to vent the Rotopax according to temperature and elevation changes to avoid pressure build-up.</li><li><strong>Regular Maintenance:</strong> Periodically check the mount and bolts for tightening to ensure everything remains secure while you traverse rugged trails.</li></ul><h2>Key Takeaways</h2><p>With this installation guide in hand, you can enhance your Jeep's functionality by adding a reliable fuel storage solution. The Rotopax system not only offers convenience but also ensures that you're prepared for extended off-road adventures. Make sure to take the time to do it right, and don’t hesitate to modify your approach based on your specific setup needs.</p>

